  
                    
                        
                
                
            England reached the semi-finals of the Hockey World Cup in India with a thrilling 3-2 victory over Argentina. Gonzalo Peillat gave Argentina the lead from a penalty corner before Barry Middleton fired in to equalise.Middleton then provided the aerial ball to set up Will Calnan put England in front.
    
        
Peillat levelled from another penalty corner but, almost immediately, Harry Martin struck the winner against the reigning Olympic champions.England will now play play Germany or Belgium in the last four.More to follow.
 
